Three Men and a Baby is a 1987 American comedy film directed by Leonard Nimoy , and stars Tom Selleck , Steve Guttenberg , Ted Danson and Nancy Travis .
It follows the mishaps and adventures of three bachelors as they attempt to adapt their lives to pseudo-fatherhood with the arrival of the love child of one of them .
The script was based on the 1985 French film Trois hommes et un couffin -LRB- Three Men and a Cradle -RRB- .
The film was the biggest American box office hit of that year , surpassing Fatal Attraction and eventually grossing US$ 170 million in the US alone .
The film won the 1988 People 's Choice Award for Favorite Comedy Motion Picture .